gov.usgs.quakeml.metadata

Class IADSRStationList

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.quakeml.metadata.IADSRStationList

  • public final class IADSRStationList
extends java.lang.Object
    This maintains a list of stations to use when parsing a particular type of email or listing to build the list of stations, their coordinates, and the FDSN network code that will be used for this station when outputing to QuakeML.
    The configuration consists of a list or priorities used when looking for a matching station in the epochs table. For instance for a simple list of preferred network codes it might look like : 
     a='NEIC' and d='USAF'
 a='FDSN' d='IM'
 a='FDSN' d='IR'
    Each query is run looking for a station match using these precidences. For each one if more than one is returned, then the choice of which one it is goes like : 
     source (DL, AL, A1),
 alias(0, 1)
 FDSN (anything but IR, IR),
 locationcode(lowest LL with -- last)
    If no station is found for each of the selections above, the next selection is run. If no station is found given all of that, it is an error and will be sent via Alarm, and noted. The QuakeML will use special code "ZZ" to indicate no network code could be found.

        Get a EventID from a Qube message stored in the qml.qube table which matches the given network, origintime and location.
        Parameters:
        net - Two character network code per qube (lower case fdsn code)
        originTime - The origin time of this quake
        lat - Latitude
        lon - Longitude
        Returns:
        Null if no matching quake is found, else the local event id
